content: Northern Siberian mountain frogs can use their tongues to measure the pH of their surrounding waters, ensuring an optimal pH balance within their delicate stomachs.
A rare species of frog from Asia can walk on its two hind legs for short periods of time, allowing it to quickly run away from predators!

content: It's impossible for frogs to choke, since they breathe and drink through their skin.
The wild Alaskan nightfang frog can jump up to two meters! Wow!
The blue poison dart frog is one of the most poisonous frogs in the world, thanks to its ability to produce poison "darts" and snipe targets with deadly accuracy.
The pink Himalayan frog is highly sought after for its special eggs, since they can be processed in salts.
The wild African jacksword frog can shoot poison out of its eyes, if startled.
Some Amazon rainforest frogs perform backflips to attract mates. Wow!
